# This repository is part of the project "Pautas para la mitigación del peligro de incendios forestales basadas en la fenología y condición estacional de los combustibles. Investigación aplicada a Chile Centro-Sur"
# The scripts contained works in python and R, and it is recommended to be run in RStudio
# For the python script, it is important to obtain the Sentinel "Tile" code of the study area (e.g. for coodinate -70.82543788,-32.60725752, the tile code is "19HCE")
# All Sentinel TILES can be obtained from the Sentinel2-grid-tiles.kml (Download from: https://hls.gsfc.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/S2A_OPER_GIP_TILPAR_MPC__20151209T095117_V20150622T000000_21000101T000000_B00.kml
# and open in Google Earth Pro software).
# The order of use each script is the following: 1. sample_points; 2. Convert_coordinates; 3. Sentinel_ts_Valparaiso; 4. Plot_timeseries; 5. Obtain phenophases (work in progress)
# Authors: Paula Basualto-Santana and Andrés Plaza-Aguilar
